
Overview of noun observation

The noun observation has 5 senses (first 5 from tagged texts)
                                    
1. (26) observation -- (the act of making and recording a measurement)
2. (6) observation, observance, watching -- (the act of observing; taking a patient look)
3. (1) observation, reflection, reflexion -- (a remark expressing careful consideration)
4. (1) observation -- (facts learned by observing; "he reported his observations to the mayor")
5. (1) notice, observation, observance -- (the act of noticing or paying attention; "he escaped the notice of the police")
